==English==
===Etymology===
From the children's story, where a little boy amuses himself by crying "[[wolf]]" to see the [[panic]] he causes in the [[community]], but does not get help when a real wolf appears.

===Verb===
'''to [[cry]] [[wolf]]'''
# To [[constantly]] warn others about an [[imagined]] [[threat]], thereby failing to get [[assistance]] when a real threat appears.

====Translations====
*French: {{t|fr|crier au loup|}}